</tbody></table><p><b>SourceDataDiskGuid (16 bytes):</b> A <b>GUID</b>,
as specified in <span><a href="../ms-dtyp/cca27429-5689-4a16-b2b4-9325d93e4ba2" data-linktype="relative-path">[MS-DTYP]</a></span>
section <span><a href="../ms-dtyp/001eec5a-7f8b-4293-9e21-ca349392db40" data-linktype="relative-path">2.3.4.2</a></span>,
that contains the resource ID of the storage class resource that is the
replication source.</p><p><b>IncludeAvailableStorageDisks (1 byte):</b> The
client sets this field to 0x01 to request that results include storage class
resources that have not yet been configured as cluster shared <span><a href="694e5e7a-5833-4f3d-b47e-323ee1d452c2#gt_9a876829-33a1-4f0b-8b81-8552b7e5561c" data-linktype="relative-path">volumes</a></span>.
Otherwise, the client sets this field to 0x00.</p><p><b>Reserved1 (1 byte):</b> This field MUST be
ignored.</p><p><b>Reserved2 (1 byte):</b> This field MUST be
ignored.</p><p><b>Reserved3 (1 byte):</b> This field MUST be
ignored.</p></div>